cale i collaborate with scientists of other disciplines to understand the links between plant biodiversity and the provision of ecosystem services as well as the socioeconomic factors that drive ecosystem management i am also developing both regional and national maps to highlight key socio ecological tradeoffs and inform decision making i really enjoy brainstorming and thinking collectively with students and colleagues i teach undergraduate and graduate courses on ecosystem services and community ecology tags biodiversity climate change coupled social ecological systems ecosystem services forests natural resource management north america sustainability tropical plant biodiversity 2012 leopold leadership program the stanford woods institute for the environment stanford university stanford ca 94305
